body:
The following config should do similar to what I described above except with the following changes: 
- every weekend instead of monthly. I figured you don't need to merge the PR, and it shouldn't hurt to just have it out there so you're aware of it, but obviously that's easy to change.
- reduced it to only 3 concurrent PR's, which helps avoid conflicts in your package lock files

```
{
  "extends": [
    "config:base"
  ],
  "baseBranches": ["dev"],
  "packageRules": [
    {
      "packagePatterns": [
        "*"
      ],
      "minor": {
        "groupName": "all non-major dependencies",
        "groupSlug": "all-minor-patch"
      }
    }
  ],
  "prHourlyLimit": 0,
  "prConcurrentLimit": 3,
  "schedule": ["every weekend"]
}
```
